div.h1: TSS ESP0 Update on Context Switch
div.p: Before returning to user mode, set TSS.ESP0 to current process's kernel_stack_top
DANGER: TSS.ESP0 still points to OLD process's kernel stack! If interrupt fires from user mode before update, CPU uses wrong stack CORRUPTION or TRIPLE FAULT

ol.li: Save old ESP to old PCB old->kernel_stack = regs
Load new ESP from new PCB switch_to(&old->kernel_stack, new->kernel_stack)
Switch page directory if needed if (old->pd != new->pd) paging_load_directory(new->pd)
Saves user SS:ESP to kernel stack
Jumps to interrupt handler Safe - uses correct kernel stack

div.p: Symptom: User process runs once, crashes on next interrupt Cause: TSS.ESP0 not updated after context switch Result: CPU uses OLD process's kernel stack

ul.li: Triple fault on interrupt from user mode Fix: ALWAYS call tss_set_kernel_stack() BEFORE switch_to() in scheduler
